{
  "texts": [
    "FairLISA [45] utilizes the classical fairness metrics: Demographic Parity (DP) [86] and Equal Opportunity (EO) [87] to measure the fairness.",
    "Log storageLog Storage aims to implement storage specification when storing generated data primarily depends on path management.",
    "Table 4 displays the path management 1).",
    "For path management of log storage, we specify <project>/temp/ directory to store logs of ongoing or failed experiments as temporary storage and <project>/archive/ directory to store logs of completed experiments as archive storage, which is convenient for users to abandon failed experiments.",
    "When it comes to a detailed experiment log, we stipulate: 1) config.json: store all configuration information; 2) <ID>.log: store training log; 3) result.json: store model evaluation result; 4) /pth/: store model parameters at each epoch or the best epoch."
  ]
}